President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Oklahoma due to a severe winter storm that occurred from October 26 to October 29, 2020. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The counties of Caddo, Canadian, Cleveland, Dewey, Grady, Kingfisher, Kiowa, Logan, Noble, Oklahoma, Payne, Pottawatomie, and Roger Mills are eligible for this funding. Traci L. Brasher has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional counties may be designated for assistance in the future. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.